item.dc:creator: @Syme Syme
item.description:
@Syme wrote:

Okay, first of all go to Run and type cmd.
There should be a command prompt coming up.
Then type there “ipconfig” no spaces and ".
Then You must see there IP Address, Subnet Mask, and Default Gateway.
Type your Default Gateway in your browser’s Address Bar.
It will ask for a Username and Password.
Type:
Username = Admin
Password = Admin
[This works for some Routers.]
